Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
scale_what_if_current(25.10)                      scale_what_if_current(25.10)

Name
       scale_what_if_current - Scales current to do what-if analysis for a hi-
       erarchical partition and assess its effect on IR drop

Syntax
       scale_what_if_current

       [-help]

       [-hierarchy  <hier_name> | -region <x1 y1 x2 y2> | -global | -inst_list
       <filename>]

       [-scale_clock_network]

       [-scale <value> | -current <value>]

       [-net <net_name>]

       [-reset]

       Scales current to do what-if analysis for a hierarchical partition  and
       assess its effect on IR drop.

Parameters
       -current <value>
              Specifies  current value in Amperes. This is used as target peak
              current for the given hierarchy and  is  then  scaled  appropri-
              ately. You cannot specify this option with -region <x1 y1 x2 y2>
              or -global options.

       -global
              Specifies current scaling to be applied to entire design.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each scale_what_if_current parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command man scale_what_if_current.

       -hierarchy <hier_name>
              Specifies the name of the hierarchical block. For example,  -hi-
              erarchy top/blockA. To specify global scaling for the design use
              "/". For example, -hierarchy /

              -hierarchy  is  a  required parameter. This parameter allows in-
              stance-based current scaling by the specified scale factor.  The
              parameter can be used to scale down peak current values.

              The use model of instance current scaling is:

              scale_what_if_current    -hierarchy   <<instance_name>>   -scale
              <<value>>

       -net <net_name>
              Scales current of the specified net.

       -inst_list <filename>
              Specifies to scale current for the specified nets. This  parame-
              ter  allows  you  to  specify  a file containing the list of in-
              stances and their scale factor.

              Use Model

              scale_what_if_current -inst_list <filename> -scale <val>

              The format of <filename> is:

              <instanceName> <scaleFactor>

              <instanceName> <scaleFactor>

              Here,

              * <val> means the global scale factor. This value will  be  used
                if  the  local or instance-specific scale factor is not speci-
                fied.

              * <scaleFactor> means the local scale factor. If both global and
                local scale factors are  specified,  the  local  scale  factor
                takes precedence.

              Default scale factor value is 1.

       -region <x1 y1 x2 y2>
              Specifies  a  region where current scaling is to be applied. The
              default unit of x and y coordinates is in microns (um).

       -reset Resets all the previous scale_what_if_current command settings.

       -scale <value>
              Specifies any value greater than 0. For example, a value of  0.5
              will scale the current in half.

              This is a required parameter.

       -scale_clock_network
              When  specified,  scales  current  for  all instances within the
              given hierarchy.

              When not specified, the software does not  scale  the  instances
              that belong to the clock network. It scales current for the rest
              of  the  instances  within  the given hierarchy to the specified
              value.

              You cannot specify this option with -region <x1  y1  x2  y2>  or
              -global options.

              This is an optional parameter.

Examples
              *

                The  following  command  scales  current  for the hierarchical
                block BLOCK_C:

                scale_what_if_current -hierarchy top/BLOCK_C -current 0.5

Related Information
